Chandler Name Meaning in English

What does the name Chandler mean? What is the meaning of the name Chandler, lucky number, lucky stone, origin and religion.

Chandler Name Meaning. English: occupational name for a maker and seller of candles, from Middle English cha(u)ndeler (Old French chandelier, Late Latin candelarius, a derivative of candela 'candle').

Chandler Name Meaning, Origin & Details

Meaning: Candle seller Short Info: Chandler was a character in American TV series "Friends", played by Matthew Perry. Details: From an English surname which was the occupational name of a candlemaker. It derives from the Old French word chandele and the Latin word candela meaning "candle". Gender: For both boy and girl, unisex, transgender, neutral gender Origin: English Religion: Christian Suitable for: Unisex / Gender neutral Hardness: Medium hard to pronounce Uniqueness: It is a common name Short & Easy: Not very short Syllables: 8 Letters and 1 Words
